rules:
- id: rule-promotion-requires-evidence
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Pattern promotion to the core architecture must be supported by strong
    evidence, ideally sourced from multiple systems or project contexts.
  title: Rule Promotion Requires Evidence
- id: rule-system-proposes-architect-decides
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The system proposes architectural changes, but all decisions must be explicitly
    reviewed and accepted, rejected, or deferred by a human architect.
  title: Rule System Proposes Architect Decides
- id: rule-heuristic-patterns-require-signals
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Every heuristic-derived pattern must include at least one linked signal
    to ensure grounding in observable data and maintain traceability.
  title: Rule Heuristic Patterns Require Signals
- id: rule-workflow-execution-model-compliance
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Runtime-native workflows must adhere to the CAS Workflow Execution Model,
    ensuring clear separation between orchestration, reasoning, and knowledge access.
  title: Rule Workflow Execution Model Compliance
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-adr-single-source-of-truth
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture Decision Records (ADR) are the authoritative source for all
    decisions; all other artifacts, including AEM and frontmatter, must be derived
    from them.
  title: Rule Adr Single Source Of Truth
- id: rule-precedence-hierarchy
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: 'Defines the mandatory resolution hierarchy for rule conflicts: Global
    Rules > Project Rules > Prompt Rules.'
  title: Rule Precedence Hierarchy
- id: rule-decision-status-drives-stage
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture item lifecycle stages (NEXT, DONE, FUTURE, etc.) must be strictly
    mapped from their respective decision status.
  title: Rule Decision Status Drives Stage
- id: rule-do-not-merge-across-architectural-layers
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Prevents consolidation or merging of patterns that reside in different
    architectural layers to maintain separation of concerns.
  title: Rule Do Not Merge Across Architectural Layers
- id: rule-aem-consistency-with-decisions
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The Architecture Evolution Map (AEM) must always reflect current ADR decisions
    and must never contain contradictory state.
  title: Rule Aem Consistency With Decisions
- id: rule-decisions-must-be-persisted
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architectural decisions must be stored as structured ADR files before they
    can be reflected in any other system artifacts.
  title: Rule Decisions Must Be Persisted
- id: rule-core-patterns-must-be-foundational
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Core patterns are reserved for foundational architectural primitives rather
    than specific implementation strategies or local context patterns.
  title: Rule Core Patterns Must Be Foundational
- id: rule-language-semantic-contract
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Mandates precise semantic standards for architectural terminology, distinguishing
    between intent, decisions, and system state.
  title: Rule Language Semantic Contract
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-decision-schema-must-be-structured
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All ADRs must use a structured YAML schema to facilitate machine processing
    and consistent rendering across the system.
  title: Rule Decision Schema Must Be Structured
- id: rule-patterns-born-as-supporting
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: New patterns must be created with a 'supporting' scope by default and cannot
    be initialized directly as 'core' patterns.
  title: Rule Patterns Born As Supporting
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-pattern-decision-lifecycle-alignment
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Ensures the interpretation of pattern maturity (knowledge evolution) is
    consistent with its governance decision status.
  title: Rule Pattern Decision Lifecycle Alignment
summary:
  global_rules: 15
  project_rules: 0
  total_rules: 15
